                    <msContents>
                        
                        <summary>
                            <p>බුද්ධවංශ දේශනාව හා අනාගතවංශ දේශනාව ත්‍රිපිටකයේ ඛුද්දක නිකායට අයත් බුද්ධවංස පාලියෙහි එයි. පාලි බුද්ධවංසය හා අනාගත වංසය  ආශ්‍රය කරගනිමින් ගෞතම බුදුරජාණන් වහන්සේගේ බුද්ධචරිතය හා පරිණිර්වාණය පිළිබඳව සිංහල භාෂාවෙන් වර්ණනා කර ඇත. එසේම අනාගතයෙහි පහල වනවා යැයි කියන මෛත්‍රී නම් බුදුරජාණන් වහන්සේ පිළිබඳවත් ඒ බුද්ධ සාසනය පහලවන කාලයේ ඉපැදීමට හේතුවන කලයුතු වූ කුසලයන් පිලිබඳවද ඒ බුද්ධසාසනය පවතින කාලයේ උපදින්නට නොහැකි වන අකුසල කර්ම පිළිබඳවත් විග්‍රහ වී ඇත. පූජාවලිය නම් දඹදෙණි යුගයේ ලිය වූ ග්‍රන්ථයෙහි කොටස්ද ඇතුළත්ව ඇත. 
                                ශ්‍රී ලංකාවේ මකුලාන නම් විහාරයකදී පොත ලියවී ඇත. පොතේ කතුවරයා ශී රාදු නම් භික්ෂුන්වහන්සේ නමක් විසිනි. 
                            </p>
                        
                            <p>The Buddhasvamsa Desanava and Anagatavamsa Desanava are originally found in the Khuddaka Nikāya of the Tripitaka, within the Buddhavaṁsa Pali. This palm-leaf manuscript is composed in Sinhala and contains excerpts from the Pujavali, which was created during the Dambadeniya era, a medieval kingdom in present-day Sri Lanka. 
                                The content of this manuscript covers the spiritual journey of Gautama the Buddha as well as the story of Metteyya, the future Buddha, while outlining the wholesome actions individuals should undertake to become part of the dispensation of Metteyya Buddha. Conversely, it describes the unwholesome actions that would exclude someone from this path. 
                                This manuscript was authored at the Makulana Temple in Sri Lanka by Ven. Śīrādunne.
                            </p>
                        
                            <p>Information provided by Ven. Kothmale Kumarakassapa Thero</p>
                        
                       <p> Paramaththa is a non-profit organisation based in Sri Lanka that is striving to develop and promote research and theological studies of
                        Theravada Buddhism, positioning its secular and religious discourse within the context of contemporary society. Paramaththa is the
                        platform of a forest monastery in North Central Sri Lanka that was established with the aspiration of sharing the sacerdotal Dhamma
                        knowledge of the most venerable forest monks with the wider society.</p>
                        
                       <p> International Centre for Theravada Buddhism UK (ICTB UK) is a UK based non-profit organisation working with Theravada Buddhist monks
                        in the world (specially in Sri Lanka), academics and scholars to provide a tangible communal platform to reinforce the practice of Theravada
                        Buddhism in the UK. A large part of our organisation's mission is to initiate and prosper an effective repository of Theravada Buddhist texts,
                        literature and cultural articles, and make them readily accessible to the public. We believe this will not only be of immense value to the
                        practitioners and devotees of Theravada Buddhism, but also prove extremely beneficial to the broader artistic development of the Buddhist culture.</p></summary>
                        
